# install
brew install mosh
https://mosh.org/#getting

# description
Mosh: the mobile shell
Mobile shell that supports roaming and intelligent local echo.
Like SSH secure shell, but allows mobility and more responsive and robust.

# usage


# cori - on a cori login node do:
locally install mosh: https://mosh.org/#getting
module load python
mamba create --prefix $HOME/.local/conda/mosh --channel conda-forge --yes mosh
echo "mosh --server $HOME/.local/conda/mosh/bin/mosh-server $USER@cori01-224.nersc.gov"
Then on your local machine, copy and paste the output of that echo command into your local terminal.
